      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=239304#M239304</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I'd love to have a loot all button when I'm recoverying from a death as well.&amp;nbsp; My guess for why we don't have it is that the loot window for all corpses is the same, check out the default UI and you'll see that there's only one "Lootwindow" file, &amp;nbsp;whether it's yours or a mob that's been killed, and putting the "loot all" button in would effect them all.&amp;nbsp; While this isn't a major issue in most cases it makes it pretty easy for someone to inadvertently, or intentionally, clean out a raid corpse with a couple mouse clicks.&amp;nbsp; I'm sure this could be overcome with some code changes but it's probably not at the top of&amp;nbsp;the priorities list.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Great idea in concept, I've been thinking the same thing for months, just not sure how difficult it would be to implement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
