      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;I don't think it's that simple. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
What should it do if you already equipped some new items and you hit&#xD;
the button? What if you foraged something?&amp;nbsp; What does it do if&#xD;
there is not enough room?&amp;nbsp; Obviously the simple solution would be&#xD;
to equip any items that you had on you before, if possible, then put&#xD;
any bags or top level items in your inv that you had before, if&#xD;
possible, then fill open bag spaces with stuff left over, if possible,&#xD;
then leave the rest on the corpse.&amp;nbsp; Still, there are more pressing&#xD;
matters I'm sure that they are working on and the possibility for item&#xD;
poofing bugs etc seems to always be there with stuff like this so while&#xD;
they have said they would like to do it (I think) it's not something&#xD;
they can just implement instantly.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
The "penalty" aspect could easily be kept by simply making a cast timer that varies based on how many items are on the corpse.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
